  "prompt": "What does \"recipient name\" mean?",
  "response": "The term **\"recipient name\"** refers to the **name of the person or entity** who is intended to receive something, such as a package, letter, email, award, or any other form of communication or item. It is used to identify the **specific individual or organization** that is the **target recipient** of the item or message.\n\nFor example:\n- In a **letter or package**, the recipient name would be the name of the person or company the item is being sent to.\n- In an **email**, the recipient name is the name of the person or group the email is addressed to.\n- In an **award or certificate**, the recipient name is the name of the person or organization being honored.\n\nIt is important to ensure the recipient name is accurate to avoid misdelivery or confusion.",
